President Trump has signed the National Defense Authorization Act for Fiscal Year 2018, which authorizes nearly $700 billion in spending for national defense. The legislation provides the largest pay raise for members of the military in eight years and includes funding for troops, national defense, homeland security, and technology. The bill passed with bipartisan support in both the House and Senate. Members of Congress have praised the signing of the bill, highlighting its importance in rebuilding military strength and supporting the men and women in uniform.